{
  "schema": "v1",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Job's Final Appeal"
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 1 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "\"I have made a covenant with my eyes." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "How then could I gaze with desire at a virgin?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 2 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "For what is the allotment of God from above,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "or the heritage from the Almighty on high?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 3 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Does not disaster come to the unjust" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and calamity to the workers of iniquity?" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 4 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Does He not see my ways" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "and count my every step?" }]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 5 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "If I have walked in falsehood" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or my foot has rushed to deceit," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 6 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "let God weigh me with honest scales," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "that He may know my integrity." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 7 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "If my steps have turned from the path," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "if my heart has followed my eyes," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or if impurity has stuck to my hands," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 8 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "then may another eat what I have sown," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "and may my crops be uprooted." }]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 9 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "If my heart has been enticed by my neighbor's wife,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "or I have lurked at his door," }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 10 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "then may my own wife grind grain for another,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and may other men sleep with her." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 11 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "For that would be a heinous crime," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "an iniquity to be judged." }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 12 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "For it is a fire that burns down to Abaddon;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "it would root out my entire harvest." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 13 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "If I have rejected the cause of my manservant or maidservant"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "when they made a complaint against me," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 14 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "what will I do when God rises to judge?" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "How will I answer when called to account?" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 15 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "Did not He who made me in the womb also make them?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Did not the same One form us in the womb?" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 16 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "If I have denied the desires of the poor" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or allowed the widow's eyes to fail," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 17 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "if I have eaten my morsel alone," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "not sharing it with the fatherless—" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 18 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "though from my youth I reared him as would a father,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "and from my mother's womb I guided the widow—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 19 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "if I have seen one perish for lack of clothing,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or a needy man without a cloak," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 20 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "if his heart has not blessed me" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "for warming him with the fleece of my sheep,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 21 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "if I have lifted up my hand against the fatherless"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "because I saw that I had support in the gate,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 22 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "then may my arm fall from my shoulder" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "and be torn from its socket." }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 23 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "For calamity from God terrifies me," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and His splendor I cannot overpower." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 24 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "If I have put my trust in gold" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or called pure gold my security," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 25 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "if I have rejoiced in my great wealth" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "because my hand had gained so much," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 26 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "if I have beheld the sun in its radiance" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or the moon moving in splendor," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 27 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "so that my heart was secretly enticed" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and my hand threw a kiss from my mouth," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 28 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "this would also be an iniquity to be judged,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "for I would have denied God on high." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 29 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "If I have rejoiced in my enemy's ruin," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or exulted when evil befell him—" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 30 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "I have not allowed my mouth to sin" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "by asking for his life with a curse—" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 31 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "if the men of my house have not said," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "'Who is there who has not had his fill?'—" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 32 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "but no stranger had to lodge on the street,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "for my door has been open to the traveler—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 33 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "if I have covered my transgressions like Adam"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "by hiding my guilt in my heart," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 34 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "because I greatly feared the crowds" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "and the contempt of the clans terrified me,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "so that I kept silent" }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "and would not go outside—" }]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 35 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Oh, that I had one to hear me!" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "Here is my signature." }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "Let the Almighty answer me;" }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "let my accuser compose an indictment." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 36 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Surely I would carry it on my shoulder" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "and wear it like a crown." }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 37 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "I would give account of all my steps;" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "I would approach Him like a prince.—" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 38 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "if my land cries out against me" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and its furrows weep together," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 39 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "if I have devoured its produce without payment"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "or broken the spirit of its tenants," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 40 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "then let briers grow instead of wheat" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and stinkweed instead of barley.\"" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "segments": [
        {
          "kind": "t",
          "text": "Thus conclude the words of Job."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
